                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Daylight dacoity near cops abode
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Gaya, Aug. 12: Twelve armed robbers today looted the home of a stone crushing unit owner, Mohammed Fakhruddin, alias Munna Babu.         
	The traders home is located in the White House Compound area  regarded as a safe zone for its proximity to residences of senior officials, including Magadh director-general of police, Gaya superintendent of police, the magistrate and judge.         
	The robbers, posing as customers, entered the traders home today around 7.15am. After briefly engaging in shoptalk, the robbers whipped out revolvers and dragged the house owner to the living area.         
	According to Munna Babu, one of the men took him at gunpoint and forced his wife to hand over the keys of an almirah. They tied the businessmen and his family and dumped them in one of the rooms. The robbers subsequently opened an almirah in the master bedroom, took out jewellery worth Rs 10 lakh belonging to the businessmans daughters and wife and Rs 1 lakh in cash.         
	After the robbery, the men feasted over soft drinks and fruits before heading to the upper storeys, from where they stole saris. Some 45 minutes later, two of the criminals overpowered Munna Babus son after he arrived home from school and snatched the cars key from the driver.         
	While one of the criminals stayed back, 11 men walked away with the looted items.         
	After others escaped, the last man left the house warning the traders son against reporting the matter to the police.                                                                                                                                                                          
